lation, up through Mitch McConnell&#x2019;s transformation of the filibuster into a routine tool of perennial gridlock&#x2014;with firsthand accounts of recent high-profile legislative fights, and a compelling argument that the key to the Senate&#x2019;s future may be found in its past." --cPublisher's description.10aUnited States.bCongress.bSenatexFreedom of debate.16a‚Etats-Unis.bCongress.bSenatexLibert‚e de parole.17aUnited States.bCongress.bSenate2fast 0aFilibusters (Political science)zUnited States. 6aObstructionnismez‚Etats-Unis. 7aFilibusters (Political science)2fast 7aUnited States2fast 7aInformational works.2lcgft 7aDocuments d'information.2rvmgf1 aZamore, Mike,eauthor.08iOnline version:aMerkley, Jeffrey A.tFilibustered!dNew York : The New Press, [2024]z1620978032w(OCoLC)1402814325  hHELD BY NCX - 160 OTHER HOLDINGS  aZ0bNCX  aBrodartbBRODn1342065091 aAU@b000075187293  aJK1161 .M47 2024wLCc1i3213008613354lSTACKSmSHEPARDrYsYtBOOKu6/3/2024